  <div class="container center">
      <h4 class="white-text"> We’re not here to antagonize or replace the programs that are already out there. Direct-enrollment can be a challenging experience, and demands personal motivation. </h4>
      <h4 class="white-text hide-on-small-only" > But for those who need another option, take a look. It might be the key to making your study abroad experience a reality.</h4>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="container">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col s6">
        <ul class="collapsible" data-collapsible="accordion">
          <li>
            <div class="collapsible-header hoverable waves-effect">
             What are the language requirements? </div>
            <div class="collapsible-body"><p> For English language programs, TOEFL scores are usually required for non-native speakers. For the other languages, proof of fluency is rarely required, but students will be expected to conduct all lectures, readings, and tests in the target language. The equivalent of B2 in the European framework is generally a sufficient level. </p></div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <div class="collapsible-header hoverable waves-effect">
                How much do these programs cost? </div>
            <div class="collapsible-body"><p> While tuition is never over $3,000 USD, costs of  flights, room and board vary significantly country to country. </p></div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <div class="collapsible-header hoverable waves-effect">
                 What kind of scholarships are available? </div>
            <div class="collapsible-body"><p> We are not aware of any funding opportunities. However, your home university may transfer financial aid, or offer closed scholarships for its students. </p></div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <div class="collapsible-header hoverable waves-effect">
                Is safety an issue?
              </div>
            <div class="collapsible-body"><p> European programs are almost certainly located in an area at least safe, and likely safer, than where you live in the United States. Safety can be an issue in South America. Stay up-to-date on U.S. State Travel Department Warnings, and do research. </p></div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <div class="collapsible-header hoverable waves-effect">
                Why aren't more countries/languages listed?
              </div>
            <div class="collapsible-body"><p>Tuition in Australia, Asia, Western Europe and Canada tends to be too expensive to be considered part of this site. As we become aware of more programs we will continue to update the list.</p></div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="col s6">
        <ul class="collapsible" data-collapsible="accordion">
          <li>
            <div class="collapsible-header hoverable waves-effect">
                What is housing like?
                </div>
            <div class="collapsible-body"><p>Most schools will provide a list of sublets available in the area near the university. Some will have student housing available.</p></div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <div class="collapsible-header hoverable waves-effect">
              What is the academic calendar like?
              </div>
            <div class="collapsible-body"><p>Thanksgiving (fall) and Spring Break (spring) are not observed, and other holidays likely will be. Note that any school in the Southern hemisphere will likely have totally different start and end dates. </p></div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <div class="collapsible-header hoverable waves-effect">
                How do I know if my school will accept the credit?</div>
            <div class="collapsible-body"><p> Most schools state their policy regarding direct enrollment programs on their study abroad web site. Note: outside of the United States, this type of exchange is often referred to as a 'free-mover' exchange or agreement.</p></div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <div class="collapsible-header hoverable waves-effect">
                 How does this site make money?</div>
            <div class="collapsible-body"><p>It doesn't. This site is maintained to provide information about study abroad options that are rarely publicized, in the interest of promoting highly immersive, low-cost programs. </p></div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <div class="collapsible-header hoverable waves-effect">
                Can I recommend you add a program I completed?
              </div>
            <div class="collapsible-body"><p>Yes! Please shoot us an e-mail at studyunbound@gmail.com</p></div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
</div>

